---
description: Architecture and coding rules for the putting performance app
alwaysApply: true
---

- Read `AGENTS.md` and `docs/product-guide.md` before major implementation work.
- Follow MVP scope only.
- Frontend stack: React + TypeScript + Vite + Tailwind.
- Backend stack: FastAPI + SQLite.
- Keep scoring logic in backend service modules.
- Do not add authentication, payments, social features, Docker, CI/CD, or cloud sync.
- Use small, testable functions.
- Prefer explicit types and clear interfaces.
- Keep the UI mobile-friendly and simple.
- Build working vertical slices instead of generating large incomplete systems.
- Add tests for scoring logic before advanced refinements.
- When given a large task, first propose a short implementation plan, then code.
- Summarise created and modified files after each major implementation step.
